{"body": "I looked into this stuff before, for building an iOS client app, with a bit of confusion on how you should deal with this. Most stack overflow answers say to remove the verification. \r\n\r\nEventually my conclusion was:\r\nOn a login/new-session action, skip verify and put the token in `response.headers[\"X-CSRF-Token\"]`. The client can then watch for the header, and send back the last one it received.\r\n\r\nI haven't tested it to any good extent, but is this a good/safe way to go about it? ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14079097", "created_at": "2013-02-25T22:07:56Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9405#issuecomment-14079097", "updated_at": "2013-02-25T22:07:56Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9405, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Dan2552", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/51f5b50028b4d67725f4ad18170a5066?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2945baa5c102a460bd804b69dc01e591.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/received_events", "gravatar_id": "51f5b50028b4d67725f4ad18170a5066", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "Dan2552", "type": "User", "id": 1478221, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ea3ebd3543c15100997f"}, "id": 14079097, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9405"}
